`That is not a typo. The original factory, the original engineers, the original production line, the physical lineage of every car built before 2003, all of it became Bentley. A respected brand. Beautiful cars. But not Rolls-Royce. Volkswagen\u2019s chairman, Ferdinand Piech, later admitted he would have preferred to keep both brands, and that the price would have been far lower had he understood what the trademark situation actually meant. Volkswagen paid 430 million pounds for a building and learned what BMW understood for 40 million. The building is not the asset. The engineers are not the asset. The production line is not the asset. The name is the asset. It was always the asset. Everything else can be rebuilt from scratch by BMW in an empty field, and it will still be Rolls-Royce, because Rolls-Royce was never a building. It was a word.`
